{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01FSY4iXxUE4gKDNQoPrQ9Gr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"HTTPS is restored. The curl returned exit code 0 and printed \"hello\".\n\n**Root cause:** The `demo-ingress` TLS secret `expired-tls-secret` contained a certificate with a validity window of Jan 1–2 2020 (deliberately expired). nginx was serving this cert, causing all TLS clients to reject it with certificate validation errors.\n\n**Fix:** Generated a new leaf certificate for `demo.example.com` signed by the same Test CA (key at `/tmp/test-ca.key`), valid through June 2028, and replaced the secret's data. nginx picked up the new cert immediately, and the curl test now completes successfully with `SSL certificate verify ok` and returns `hello`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1388,"cache_read_input_tokens":53780,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1388},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4563f6e3-984e-4c4a-bf2b-80e8a7a877d9","uuid":"85766677-d183-4b60-a485-b1d3b6a23d8f","request_id":"req_011CcMTr3obffLDseEhLE3kE"}
